response: "{ \"title\": \"Medium: Sum of Unique Elements\", \"description\": \"Given a list of integers, calculate the sum of all unique elements. Write a function `sum_unique` that computes this sum.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef sum_unique(numbers: List[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `numbers` (List[int]): A list of integers with potential duplicates.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of all unique elements in the input list.\\n\", \"code\": \"from typing import List\\n\\ndef sum_unique(numbers: List[int]) -> int:\\n    # Create a set to store unique numbers and calculate the sum\\n    return sum(set(numbers))\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert sum_unique([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1]) == 15\", \"assert sum_unique([]) == 0\", \"assert sum_unique([7]) == 7\"] }"
